    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Prices for Storefront Products with Price Lists\n Set Up Promotions for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Enable Promotions for Your Storefront\n Best Practices When Creating Promotions for Your Storefront\n Link a Promotion to a Category\n Link a Promotion to a Product\n Link a Promotion to a Custom URL\n Add a Promotion Image from a Content Delivery Network\n Add a Promotion Image from a Static Resource\n Attach a Promotion Image Directly to a Record\n Target a Promotion at Specific Storefront Users\n Open a Document Attachment from a Storefront Promotion\n Localize Promotions for an Internationalized Storefront\n Offer Coupons for Discounts on Storefront Purchases\n Offer Subscriptions for Products on Your Storefront\n Honor Custom Prices Negotiated in a Contract\n Adjust Product Prices Based on Tiered Quantities\n Host a Seller Marketplace on Your Storefront\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nSet Up Promotions for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nAdvertise new products, offer discounts, up-sell and cross-sell products, or drive traffic to a particular page by setting up a promotion that displays on your storefront. A promotion is an image that links to another destination, such as a product, category, custom page, or external URL.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’20 (version 4.12)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’19 (version 4.11)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’19 (version 4.10)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’18 (version 4.9)\n\nYou can have your promotion appear on multiple storefront pages, and you can specify where on the page you want the promotion image to display. Set up a promotion in advance, and have it automatically begin and end at times you specify. You can also scope a promotion to target a specific group of storefront users.\n\nEnable Promotions for Your Storefront\nBefore you can start using promotions, update your storefront configuration settings.\nBest Practices When Creating Promotions for Your Storefront\nWhen you set up a promotion, decide where the promotion appears on your storefront and how you specify the source image file for the promotion.\nLink a Promotion to a Category\nCreate a promotion on your storefront that links to the Product List page for a particular category. For example, let's say that you want to promote all espresso products on your storefront. You can create a promotion that links to a list of all products that belong to the Espresso category. A buyer can quickly select from all available espresso products.\nLink a Promotion to a Product\nCreate a promotion on your storefront that links to a particular Product Detail page. For example, let's say that you sell a particular style of espresso machine and you want to clear out unused inventory. You can create a promotion that links to the espresso machine's details, so that a buyer can quickly add the espresso machine to their cart.\nLink a Promotion to a Custom URL\nCreate a promotion on your storefront that links to a URL you specify. For example, if you want to drive traffic to an event registration page hosted on another site, you can create a promotion that opens that link.\nAdd a Promotion Image from a Content Delivery Network\nYou can reference an image file served from a central file repository, such as content delivery network (CDN), using a uniform resource identifier (URI). We recommend this option for your image files whenever possible because it's the easiest way to maintain your images from a single managed location.\nAdd a Promotion Image from a Static Resource\nYou can reference an image file included in a static resource when specifying the image for a promotion. You can bundle multiple image files together in a single static resource, and reference the static resources across multiple records.\nAttach a Promotion Image Directly to a Record\nYou can attach an image file directly to a CC Promotion record.\nTarget a Promotion at Specific Storefront Users\nTo control which storefront users can see a particular promotion, you can show or hide promotions by account group.\nOpen a Document Attachment from a Storefront Promotion\nYou can set up a promotion that opens an attached document, such as a PDF or text file. For example, maybe you want a promotion to open a document that explains rules, terms, or other details about your promotion.\nLocalize Promotions for an Internationalized Storefront\nIf your storefront supports more than one locale, localize your promotion records for each of your supported languages. You can specify a unique promotion image for each locale so that you create a truly localized experience for your storefront users.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
